Practice takes place in recording studios according to the contracts with the UT VCA. Practice aims at making students flexible in adapting to different acoustics and different recording possibilities. A report is submitted on the equipment and recording principles applied.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Develop the students' skills, on the basis of their prior theoretical knowledge, to record groups performing a variety of music styles in the recording studio. To develop ability to communicate with musicians and performers and to ensure individual skills to work with different projects and to find the best solutions how to solve them.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course students should: * have the experience in working independently with smaller projects in the studio * have thorough knowledge of sound processing and amplifying, sound recording and editing * knows well different recording systems and knows how to use it in different recording situations * can lead recording process  * has knowledge for working in live situation * is able to plan appropriate solution for concert or performance and can process it independently
